The paper discusses the use of game theory for the design of distributed algorithms, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses resource allocation, which is a common topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of optimization techniques and linear programming is also mentioned, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the price-of-anarchy, which is a common metric in network economics (cs.NE).
